ned another 14 priests in Rivne and Sarny dioceses as part of a probe on charges of high treason and inciting religious hatred. Tensions over the church come amid a bitter tug-of-war between the two neighbors that began with Russia's 2014 annexation of Crimea and support for separatist insurgents in eastern Ukraine. The rift escalated further after a naval incident on Nov. 25 in which the Russian coast guard fired on and seized three Ukrainian navy vessels. Poroshenko responded by declaring 30-day martial law in much of Ukraine. A previous version of this story was corrected to show that the date of the meeting as Dec. 15, not Dec. 5."	nonTerrorism	Religion
