e dead in March 2016. In August that same year, a machete-wielding man shouting ""Allahu Akbar"" attacked two policewomen in the industrial town of Charleroi before being shot dead. The country's law enforcement agencies and intelligence services came under intense scrutiny for apparently missing a series of leads after the Paris attacks that could have led to the Brussels bombers. "	Terrorism	Terrorism
