oup in Basilan, Southern Philippines) was arrested in a counter terrorism operation on Mar 15. ""The suspect had a very good and close relationship with Dr Mahmud Ahmad (A Malaysian militant who joined IS in the Phillipines). “He was also on the Phillipines government's wanted list for several kidnapping for ransom cases and attempted murders,” he said, adding the militant was an expert in making improvised explosive devices (IED). Fuzi said all those detained were being investigated for having links with terrorist groups and had been held under the Security Offences (Special Measures) Act 2012 (Sosma) and Section 574 of the Penal Code."	Terrorism	Terrorism
